<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,385,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
This taxon was listed as a synonym of either 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[691,836,457,483]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edusa">
<emphasis box="[691,836,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pontia edusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." box="[897,1154,456,483]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref6289" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei. 3 Vols. Wagener, Bocholt, 2001 pp. [pp. 1 - 754 + 755 - 1154 + 1 - 847]" type="book chapter" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis box="[1035,1090,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
, 1: 426) or of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garcia-Barros et al. 2013, p. 960)" baseAuthorityName="Garcia-Barros" baseAuthorityPageNumber="960" baseAuthorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pieris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daplidice">
<emphasis box="[1306,1436,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">P. daplidice</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia-Barros, E. &amp; Munguira, M. L. &amp; Stefanescu, C. &amp; Vives Moreno, A." box="[159,450,493,519]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 1213" refId="ref5886" refString="Garcia-Barros, E., Munguira, M. L., Stefanescu, C. &amp; Vives Moreno, A. (2013) Lepidoptera Papilionoidea. In: Fauna Iberica. Vol. 37. Museo nacional de Ciencias naturales y Consejo superior de Investigaciones cientificas, Madrid, pp. 1 - 1213, 147 pls." type="book chapter" year="2013">
García-Barros 
<emphasis box="[327,377,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 960)
</taxonomicName>
, respectively for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[883,963,493,519]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and for that of 
<collectingCountry box="[1141,1208,493,519]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Spain</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kudrna, O." box="[1219,1432,492,519]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref7065" refString="Kudrna, O. (1983) An annotated catalogue of the butterflies named by Roger Verity. The Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera, 21, 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1983">Kudrna (1983: 58)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagener, S." box="[151,379,528,555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="21 - 38" refId="ref7846" refString="Wagener, S. (1988) What are the valid names for the two genetically different taxa currently included within Pontia daplidice (Linnaeus, 1758)? (Lepidoptera: Pieridae). Nota lepidopterologica, 11 (1), 21 - 38." type="journal article" year="1988">Wagener (1988: 35)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." box="[438,781,528,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref6289" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei. 3 Vols. Wagener, Bocholt, 2001 pp. [pp. 1 - 754 + 755 - 1154 + 1 - 847]" type="book chapter" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis box="[579,631,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al</emphasis>
. (1995: 426)
</bibRefCitation>
regarded “nitida” Verity, 1908 as an unavailable infrasubspecific name. However, Art. 45.6.4 states that [the rank denoted by a species-group name following a binomen] “is subspecific if first published before 1961 and its author expressly used one of the terms “variety” or “form” …, unless its author also expressly gave it infrasubspecific rank, or the content of the work unambiguously reveals that the name was proposed for an infrasubspecific entity …”. Verity wrote: “[dans les régions] qui semblent être surtout les plus arides (telles que l’Espagne, l’Algérie et l’Asie Mineure) [
<taxonomicName box="[884,1061,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pieris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daplidice">
<emphasis box="[884,1061,709,735]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pieris daplidice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] semble avoir une tendance à être plus petit, à avoir les ailes plus larges, le limbe externe plus convexe, les dessins d’un noir plus profond et à contours plus arrêtés …”. The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Verity, 1908" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1908" box="[459,906,781,807]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pieris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="daplidice" subSpecies="nitida">
<emphasis box="[459,636,781,807]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pieris daplidice</emphasis>
race 
<emphasis box="[697,762,781,807]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">nitida</emphasis>
Verity, 1908
</taxonomicName>
is therefore available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,385,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
The originally designated 
<typeStatus box="[494,592,817,843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">syntypes</typeStatus>
probably belong to two separate species, but no 
<typeStatus box="[1143,1246,817,843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">lectotype</typeStatus>
was validly designated by any of the preceding authors under Art. 74. Both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[836,1023,853,879]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daplidice">
<emphasis box="[836,1023,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pontia daplidice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[1079,1173,853,879]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edusa">
<emphasis box="[1079,1173,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">P. edusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may possibly co-occur in parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[273,353,889,915]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Geiger, H. J. &amp; Descimon, H. &amp; Scholl, A." box="[413,620,889,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="7 - 20" refId="ref5946" refString="Geiger, H. J., Descimon, H. &amp; Scholl, A. (1988) Evidence for speciation within nominal Pontia daplidice (Linnaeus, 1758) in southern Europe (Lepidoptera: Pieridae). Nota lepidopterologica, 11 (1), 7 - 20." type="journal article" year="1988">
Geiger 
<emphasis box="[497,553,889,915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." box="[631,891,888,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref6289" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei. 3 Vols. Wagener, Bocholt, 2001 pp. [pp. 1 - 754 + 755 - 1154 + 1 - 847]" type="book chapter" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis box="[771,828,889,915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="John, E. &amp; Wiemers, M. &amp; Makris, C. &amp; Russell, P." box="[946,1131,889,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="69 - 78" refId="ref6939" refString="John, E., Wiemers, M., Makris, C. &amp; Russell, P. (2013) The Pontia daplidice (Linnaeus, 1758) / Pontia edusa (Fabricius, 1777) complex (Lepidoptera: Pieridae): confirmation of the presence of Pontia daplidice in Cyprus, and of Cleome iberica DC. as a new host plant for this species in the Levant. Entomologist's Gazette, 64 (2), 69 - 78." type="journal article" year="2013">
John 
<emphasis box="[1007,1064,889,915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), while only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1278,1410,889,915]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daplidice">
<emphasis box="[1278,1410,889,915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">P. daplidice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[361,428,925,951]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Spain</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,385,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
We therefore designate the 
<specimenCount box="[502,523,961,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[529,621,961,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Syntype</typeStatus>
in MZUF from: [
<collectingCountry box="[815,915,960,987]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Spanien</collectingCountry>
]: 
<collectingRegion box="[930,1062,961,987]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Andalusien</collectingRegion>
: Malaga, C. Ribbe [legit], as Lec- totype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Verity, 1908" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1908" box="[260,710,997,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pieris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="daplidice" subSpecies="nitida">
<emphasis box="[260,438,997,1023]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Pieris daplidice</emphasis>
race 
<emphasis box="[500,565,997,1023]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">nitida</emphasis>
Verity, 1908
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[770,859,997,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1718,1743]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,191,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,179,1691]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. (A). Lectotype (♂) of Pieris daplidice race nitida Verity, 1908: (d) dorsal (v) ventral (MZUF). (B). Neotype (♀) of [Papilio] ausonia Hübner, [1804]: (d) dorsal (v) ventral) (MZUF). (C). Centre: Original Freyer’s sealed box containing the Neotype (♂) of Pontia simplonia Freyer, 1829 (bottom right), together with a female of the same species (top left); Left: electronically extracted enlargement of the Neotype (♂) (d) dorsal (JME). (D). Lectotype (♂) of Euchloe crameri Butler, 1869 as designated by Rothschild (1914) (NHMUK). (E). Lectotype (♂) of Euchloe ausonia var. esperi Kirby, 1871 (5) (NMI). Labels relative to the illustrated specimens are shown on the right of each row." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842458/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Consequently, the latter name becomes fixed as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[486,862,1032,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daplidice">
<emphasis box="[486,679,1033,1059]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Papilio daplidice</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1758
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
